tags: richard!tennant is the most beautiful tennant
'medium height' is surprising though as he appears to be ten feet tall
title: on a cheerier note
body:
Everyone once in a while I remember that I have a copy of the official character descriptions from the audio-described performances of the RSC Richard II and then I feel the need to share the description of Richard because it is so delightfully fangirly:

Played by David Tennant, KING RICHARD II is an attractive man, tense with nervous energy. He is about 40, of medium height and very thin. He is clean shaven and his sharp features, prominent cheekbones and aquiline nose, together with his particularly bright, large eyes, give him the look of a bird of prey. His habit of cocking his head to one side and fixing his gaze increases this resemblance. His long, shining, chestnut tresses flow over his shoulders and halfway down his back. He can be proud, severe, mischievous, quick-witted or self-absorbed and change, like lightning, from one to the other. His mercurial character is also expressed in his movements which can be agile and swift or maintain a statue-like stillness. His hands are particularly fine and expressive, with long, tapered fingers.

He first appears in a floor-length robe of gold brocade topped with a flowing silk mantle. He wears the royal crown, a gold circlet with a design of fleur-de-lis, and cradles the sceptre in the crook of his arm.

When enthroned, he is resplendent in cloth of gold, with the crown on his head and holding sceptre and orb. He also sometimes appears in pale blue, pleated silk and a robe of brighter blue. Under the different robes he wears a simple, loose, linen shirt, which ties at the neck and narrow leggings. Later he wears only a plain, long, white, collarless gown with wide, flaring sleeves which almost cover his hands. A gold cross on a chain hangs round his neck and his feet are bare.
